2pm 29 December 1999
KTRU was great fun today! I recorded my show (recorded 2 hours of my 3 hour show) for Channing, a youth in Tulsa, who was really excited to expand his musical awareness! I think Side A is more musically expanding&hellip;
But!! The coolest thing: A guy called in; &ldquo;Will you play something by Squarepusher?&rdquo; (I gave my standard non-committal answer; I didn&rsquo;t know if I could find it).

15:46 Saturday 21 August 1999
Last night (and every Friday night) KTRU broadcast MK Ultra show - 3 hours of live DJs mixing jungle or techno or breakbeat or any basic rave music. I love the show so I go to watch the DJs spin and basically just think, &ldquo;wow! [I wonder if I would enjoy spending enough time to get that good?]&rdquo;
Last night Chris Anderson was spinning; he&rsquo;s big in the Houston rave scene and maybe way bigger than that; I know he&rsquo;s spinning in Santa Fe tonight.

6:54am Tuesday 17 August 1999
Today I have jury duty. The summons came by mail to my apartment while I was in Iowa. When I saw the summons, I was like, &ldquo;uh oh- I hope I didn&rsquo;t miss it!&rdquo;
I didn&rsquo;t miss it. But I did miss the fact that I am scheduled for KTRU on the same day. Doh! I caught this too late and requested a sub only a couple days ago.

7:12pm Thursday 8 April 1999
Aw man, first, super duper special thanks to Wende for reminding me last night that today is Thursday and I was supposed to work at KTRU!!!! I had totally forgotten it, and she mentioned it offhandedly (whatever that is supposed to mean) and I was like, &ldquo;!!!!!!!!!&rdquo;
Wende and I had just eaten at Dude and Veronica&rsquo;s house and it was gettin&rsquo; late. We still had to go to Sterling McCall to get Scott after he had his timing belt and water pump replaced.

5 April 1999
On Saturday morning I was on at KTRU from 7 to 9am. On the way driving there, only static was on the station; that meant no one was there. This brings to mind one question for me: &ldquo;will I be able to get into the station?&rdquo;
More specifically, will I be able to get into the building in which the station is located? I&rsquo;m not a student at Rice University, so I don&rsquo;t have a card that will let me into the building if it&rsquo;s locked.
